b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe15035.htm)  [Next](sbe15037.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBWG/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 2 (SBE15)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 56\n\n### THIRD ANUV\xc3\x82KA.\n\n'The Devas breathe after breath (pra _n_ a), so do men and cattle. Breath is\nthe life of beings, therefore it is called sarvayusha (all-enlivening).'\n\nThey who worship breath as Brahman, obtain the full life. For breath is the\nlife of all beings, and therefore it is called sarvayusha. The embodied Self\nof this (consisting of breath) is the same as that of the former (consisting\nof food).\n\nDifferent from this, which consists of breath, is the other, the inner Self,\nwhich consists of mind. The former is filled by this. It also has the shape of\nman. Like the human shape of the former is the human shape of the latter. Ya\n_g_ us is its head. _Ri_ _k_ is its right arm. Saman is its left arm. The\ndoctrine (ade _s_ a, i.e. the Brahma _n_ a) is its trunk. The Atharva\xe1\xb9\x85giras\n(Atharva-hymns) the seat (the support).\n\nOn this there is also the following _S_ loka:\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: II, 4](sbe15037.htm)\n\n"